qas.question: Who established Christianity in the region?
What did the Frankish expansion and the Bavarian expansion introduce?
What area still has intricate frescoes?

answers.text: Castello del Buonconsiglio in Trento, Italy

qas.question: What is preserved as an example of medieval architecture?

context: Christianity was established in the region by the <a0_0>Romans<a0_0/>, and saw the establishment of monasteries and churches in the high regions. The Frankish expansion of the Carolingian Empire and the Bavarian expansion in the eastern Alps introduced <a1_0>feudalism<a1_0/> and the building of castles to support the growing number of dukedoms and kingdoms. <a2_0>Castello del Buonconsiglio in Trento, Italy<a2_0/>, still has intricate frescoes, excellent examples of Gothic art, in a tower room. In Switzerland, <a3_0>Château de Chillon<a3_0/> is preserved as an example of medieval architecture.
